Pacific gecko
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a particularly timid gecko, widespread in the North Island especially from Taupo north and west.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Hoplodactylus pacificus</i>
Citations
Date: 0/0/2002
Source: NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page: 55/13
Edition:
Quote: Among the 14 or so species of reptile on Little Barrier are Duvaucel's gecko (at up to 25 cm, including the tail, one of the largest geckos in the world) the very rare chevron skink (found only on Little and Great Barrier islands), and the Pacific gecko, seen here licking nectar from a pohutukawa blossom.
